slot.

01:22.416 --> 01:24.384 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
John Yang begins our coverage.

01:24.418 --> 01:30.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Throughout the
campaign, Jared
Kushner had Donald Trump's ear
and now the

01:30.290 --> 01:34.194 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
president wants him to follow
him to the White
House as a top adviser.

01:34.227 --> 01:40.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Like the president-elect,
Kushner, who turns
36 tomorrow, is the son of a
real estate magnate.

01:40.033 --> 01:47.341 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He became CEO of Kushner
Companies, his father's
multibillion-dollar business, in
2008.

01:47.374 --> 01:49.910 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In 2009, he married Ivanka
Trump.

01:49.943 --> 01:55.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Trump insiders credit Kushner
with restructuring
and modernizing his
father-in-law's campaign.

01:55.849 --> 02:00.320 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
During the transition, he's been
involved
in key personnel decisions.

02:00.354 --> 02:05.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Former Secretary of State Henry
Kissinger
told "Forbes" magazine: "Every
president I

02:05.425 --> 02:10.831 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have ever known has one or two
people he intuitively
and structurally trusts.

02:10.864 --> 02:14.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think Jared might be that
person."

02:14.101 --> 02:18.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even with president-elect
Trump's confidence,
Kushner could face hurdles
before he can assume

02:18.772 --> 02:20.407 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a White House post.

02:20.440 --> 02:24.077 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
