07:13.333 --> 07:18.672 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: The
president-elect walked
out of Trump Tower with a
business leader,

07:18.705 --> 07:24.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Jack Ma of the Chinese
e-commerce giant Alibaba,
but his words were about
politics and his

07:24.511 --> 07:25.812 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Cabinet nominees.

07:25.845 --> 07:27.747 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP (R),
President-Elect: I think
they will all pass.

07:27.781 --> 07:31.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: That after
Trump met with
a key ally, Senate Majority
Leader Mitch McConnell,

07:31.951 --> 07:33.753 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who dismissed concerns about
vetting.

07:33.787 --> 07:35.522 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

07:35.555 --> 07:37.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: Yes,
everybody will be properly
vetted, as they

07:37.357 --> 07:40.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
