conflict of interest
doesn't matter.

10:04.571 --> 10:09.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For instance, Rex Tillerson
filed in his letter,
which we now have, that he will
go ahead and

10:09.175 --> 10:15.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not just not get a salary from
ExxonMobil,
but any future bonuses which
were significant,

10:15.348 --> 10:18.485 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he's going to now sever ties
with altogether
from ExxonMobil.

10:18.518 --> 10:22.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And as we have
been saying,
some of these nominees have
these very complicated

10:22.655 --> 10:24.324 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
financial backgrounds.

10:24.357 --> 10:28.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want to ask you about what the
director
of the Office of Government
Ethics wrote in

10:29.028 --> 10:30.763 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
