29:07.679 --> 29:13.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Since Harry
Truman, every Democratic
president has dreamed about
universal coverage.

29:13.852 --> 29:18.256 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jonathan Oberlander, a health
policy historian
at the University of North
Carolina at Chapel

29:18.290 --> 29:23.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hill, says Obama succeeded in
winning over
health care interest groups that
had fought

29:23.061 --> 29:24.796 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
previous reform attempts.

29:24.830 --> 29:28.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the bill became a flash
point for bigger
ideological battles.

29:28.200 --> 29:29.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JONATHAN OBERLANDER, Professor
of Social Medicine,
Health Policy and Management,
University of

29:30.002 --> 29:34.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
North Carolina: In key respects,
it was a
policy success, but it was also
always a political

29:34.172 --> 29:36.908 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
failure since 2010.

29:36.942 --> 29:41.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that political failure
reflects that partisan
polarization, which Democrats
and the Obama

29:41.780 --> 29:46.918 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
administration never figured out
a way to
overcome.

29:46.952 --> 29:53.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: The bill passed
without a single
Republican vote and would face
unflagging

29:53.158 --> 29:55.961 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
opposition, explosive town hall
meetings

29:55.994 --> 29:59.965 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: If you let the free
market system work,
everybody could have insurance.

29:59.998 --> 30:01.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Angry Tea Party
protests.

30:01.833 --> 30:03.568 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PROTESTERS: Obamacare has got to
go!

30:03.602 --> 30:05.404 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PROTESTERS: What do we want?

30:05.437 --> 30:07.205 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PROTESTERS: Health care!

30:07.239 --> 30:11.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: And a Supreme
Court decision
in 2012 that, despite upholding
most of the

30:11.476 --> 30:16.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
