News of food arriving sends
these civilians
displaced by the battle for
Mosul into a frenzy,

39:18.156 --> 39:23.394 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
charging this truck, as
desperate hands reach
out to catch bread and water,
talk to a mob

39:23.428 --> 39:25.396 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of hungry people.

39:25.430 --> 39:30.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The camps were supposed to be
temporary solution,
yet families here are facing
what now promises

39:30.969 --> 39:33.404 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to be a very long winter.

39:33.438 --> 39:36.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's painfully cold, down to
freezing temperatures
at night.

39:36.841 --> 39:42.280 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Toxic fumes from the gas stoves
and heaters
permeate the tents.

39:42.313 --> 39:47.352 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Yet, in this corner of the camp,
we found
a reason to smile.

39:47.385 --> 39:54.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These are sounds most of these
children have
not made in almost
two-and-a-half years.

39:54.092 --> 39:57.528 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Every day, the children clamor
at the gates
of this child-friendly space.

39:57.562 --> 40:04.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They get a precious six hours a
week here
to play, sing and learn, a far
cry from the

40:04.702 --> 40:06.738 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
horrors of ISIS.

40:06.771 --> 40:09.974 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We sat down with a few students
in the drawing
tent.

40:10.008 --> 40:15.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Like most children, 13-year-old
Zuha stopped
going to school when ISIS came
to Mosul and

40:15.280 --> 40:17.482 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
missed out on things like
drawing.

40:17.515 --> 40:19.684 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now she draws her memories of
home.

40:19.717 --> 40:23.388 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ZUHA, Student (through
translator): We had
a garden, so I draw flowers.

40:23.421 --> 40:28.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Twelve-year-old
Bishara did
stay in school under ISIS, which
used militarization

40:28.493 --> 40:32.297 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and indoctrination as part of
its lesson plan.

40:32.330 --> 40:36.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In these pages of a math book,
children are
asked to solve problems about
setting land

40:36.934 --> 40:38.936 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
mines and killing nonbelievers.

40:38.970 --> 40:42.774 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BISHARA, Student (through
translator): After
ISIS came, I stayed in school
one-and-a-half

40:42.807 --> 40:43.775 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
years.

40:43.808 --> 40:45.276 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Everything changed.

40:45.310 --> 40:47.111 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
In math, the curriculum changed.

40:47.145 --> 40:48.313 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thy used bullets.

40:48.346 --> 40:51.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Like, one bullet plus two
bullets equals three
bullets.

40:51.382 --> 40:53.384 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Was that scary?

40:53.418 --> 40:55.320 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BISHARA (through translator):
Yes, it was
so scary.

40:55.353 --> 40:59.891 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: She finally asked
her parents
to remove her from school, but
she still has

40:59.924 --> 41:01.192 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
big dreams.

41:01.225 --> 41:05.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I asked her what she wants to be
when she
grows up.

41:05.563 --> 41:08.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You want to be a doctor?

41:08.833 --> 41:11.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Like many of the children, she's
drawing an
Iraqi flag.

41:11.402 --> 41:17.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It says, "I love Iraq," words
forbidden under
the Islamic State, where the
Iraqi flag was

41:17.675 --> 41:21.079 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
banned and members of the Iraqi
army executed.

41:21.112 --> 41:25.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Twelve-year-old Mohamed wants to
be an artist
someday and is proud of his
flag.

41:25.149 --> 41:27.885 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He had two uncles in the Iraqi
police force.

41:27.919 --> 41:30.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MOHAMED, Student (through
translator): They
killed two of my uncles they
worked for the

41:30.688 --> 41:32.123 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
police.

41:32.156 --> 41:34.225 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIS killed anyone from the
police.

41:34.258 --> 41:36.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Did you spend a
lot of time
with your uncles?

41:36.928 --> 41:38.096 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Were you really close with them?

41:38.129 --> 41:39.497 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MOHAMED (through translator):
Yes.

41:39.530 --> 41:40.665 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
They loved me.

41:40.698 --> 41:42.934 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They used to bring me toys.

41:42.967 --> 41:45.370 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
My father and I used to play
hide and seek
with them.

41:45.403 --> 41:48.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Were you get
scared that maybe
your father might be hurt too?

41:48.506 --> 41:49.540 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MOHAMED (through translator):
Yes.

41:49.574 --> 41:53.378 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I am worried about my father and
brothers.

41:53.411 --> 41:56.347 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Almost all of my uncles were
police, so my
father was afraid.

41:56.381 --> 41:59.250 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: It's a familiar
fear.

41:59.283 --> 42:04.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we spoke, 12-year-old Mahmoud
was clearly
distressed, but wanted very much
to talk.

42:04.856 --> 42:09.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAHMOUD, Student (through
translator): ISIS
was in Mosul for about
two-and-a-half years.

42:09.060 --> 42:13.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When they came to the city, we
thought they
were good and they wouldn't hurt
us.

42:13.264 --> 42:15.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But they began to kill and
torture people.

42:15.600 --> 42:16.901 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's why we hated them.

42:16.934 --> 42:19.670 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Anyone you know
was hurt?

42:19.704 --> 42:23.241 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAHMOUD (through translator): I
didn't see,
and I don't want to see.

42:23.274 --> 42:25.143 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It was horrible and scary.

42:25.176 --> 42:30.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: He says he loved
math and reading
before ISIS came, and still
wants to be an

42:30.515 --> 42:32.350 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
engineer.

42:32.383 --> 42:35.019 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAHMOUD (through translator):
I'm comfortable
now that I am back to learning
and studying.

42:35.052 --> 42:36.954 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I can study now, which is good.

42:36.988 --> 42:37.955 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm relieved.

42:37.989 --> 42:40.324 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Do you feel safe
here?

42:40.358 --> 42:41.793 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAHMOUD (through translator):
Yes.

42:41.826 --> 42:43.194 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Here, I feel safe.

42:43.227 --> 42:46.531 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are people protecting us,
guarding us.

42:46.564 --> 42:49.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we still live in a tent, and
it rains
a lot.

42:49.200 --> 42:51.035 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's really affecting us.

42:51.068 --> 42:56.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: He echoes a fear
we heard again
and again from the mothers in
the camp, the

42:56.407 --> 43:03.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
terror of ISIS replaced by an
unknown future
in a tent at the beginning of a
cold, wet

43:03.047 --> 43:04.649 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
winter.

43:04.682 --> 43:07.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Twenty-old-year-old Hijran
Tantafati (ph)
was an officer in the Iraqi
police.

43:07.852 --> 43:11.355 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When ISIS took Mosul, seven men
came to their
door for him.

43:11.389 --> 43:16.694 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HIJRAN, Iraq (through
translator): They executed
my husband because he was a
policeman working

43:16.727 --> 43:18.062 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for the Iraqi government.

43:18.095 --> 43:20.932 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he wouldn't give up his
weapons and surrender.

43:20.965 --> 43:25.703 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They killed all the policemen
because they
said they were nonbelievers.

43:25.736 --> 43:30.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They finally gave us the body a
month after
he died, but they wouldn't allow
us to have

43:30.374 --> 43:32.243 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a proper funeral.

43:32.276 --> 43:37.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Suddenly, a widow
with two children,
no money, and no job, she was
devastated,

43:37.715 --> 43:39.650 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but too afraid to speak out.

43:39.684 --> 43:43.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If she ventured outside the
house without
strict Islamic clothing, ISIS
would torture

43:43.754 --> 43:46.224 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
her male relatives.

43:46.257 --> 43:50.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hijran and her children are here
with her
older sister, Hiba, and her
family.

43:50.361 --> 43:55.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They fled Mosul after Iraqi
forces backed
by coalition airstrikes pushed
ISIS from their

43:55.533 --> 43:57.335 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
neighborhood.

43:57.368 --> 44:00.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They still have two sisters and
three brothers
in Mosul, so they have covered
their faces

44:00.838 --> 44:07.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to protect them from retribution
-- public
torture and execution made
routine under ISIS.

44:07.111 --> 44:09.514 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How did you explain this to your
children?

44:09.547 --> 44:11.616 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How did you try to protect them
from this?

44:11.649 --> 44:14.185 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HIBA, Iraq (through translator):
I didn't
let them do anything.

44:14.218 --> 44:16.487 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I even banned them from going to
school.

44:16.521 --> 44:18.890 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I didn't let them go outside.

44:18.923 --> 44:23.694 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I would see torturing in the
market, cutting
off hands, cutting off a head.

44:23.728 --> 44:25.563 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They used a lot of torture.

44:25.596 --> 44:29.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, thank God, I didn't let the
children
see any of it.

44:29.367 --> 44:34.171 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Hiba became
pregnant last year
and entered a deep depression.

44:34.205 --> 44:38.676 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She gave birth to baby Karam at
home just
over a month before we met, with
her husband

44:38.709 --> 44:43.014 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and sister by her side, as
coalition airstrikes
thundered down.

44:43.047 --> 44:45.917 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HIBA (through translator): It
was the hardest
day in my life.

44:45.950 --> 44:48.352 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I was so scared and confused.

44:48.386 --> 44:51.255 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But God made it easy for me, and
I gave birth.

44:51.289 --> 44:53.257 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The houses were being bombed,
and I was so
scared.

44:53.291 --> 44:57.061 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Are you afraid of
the life that
he's been brought into?

44:57.094 --> 45:00.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HIBA (through translator): I'm
worried about
the weather and the cold
temperatures here.

45:00.698 --> 45:04.201 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Of course I'm afraid for him,
for so many
reasons.

45:04.235 --> 45:08.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: Aid organizations
expected more
people at camps like these, but
for a much

45:08.940 --> 45:10.675 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
shorter time.

45:10.708 --> 45:14.579 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
As the battle for Mosul
continues to grind
on with no end in sight, those
fleeing the

45:14.612 --> 45:19.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
battle continue to arrive in
droves, and it
doesn't look like they are going
anywhere

45:19.116 --> 45:20.885 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
anytime soon.

45:20.918 --> 45:25.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Maulid Warfa heads operations at
UNICEF in
Irbil, which runs the
child-friendly space.

45:25.923 --> 45:30.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says his main concern is the
duration of
the battle and the fact that the
camps were

45:30.127 --> 45:34.265 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
set up as emergency measures,
without proper
schools in the plans.

45:34.298 --> 45:39.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAULID WARFA, UNICEF: What
worries me the
most is to have these children
roaming around

45:39.270 --> 45:45.076 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with no proper schooling, with
no proper protection,
losing their future.

45:45.109 --> 45:46.644 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Imagine if these were your
children.

45:46.677 --> 45:48.546 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do you want your children
to be?

45:48.579 --> 45:52.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You want them to be going to
school, you want
them to be children again, you
want them to

45:52.249 --> 45:58.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be protected, you want them to
be loved, you
want them to be growing up as
very peaceful

45:58.356 --> 46:00.057 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
human beings.

46:00.091 --> 46:05.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: The longer the war
grinds on,
the longer these families remain
trapped in

46:05.496 --> 46:10.501 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what human rights organizations
are calling
de facto detention centers.

46:10.534 --> 46:15.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we drove up to the camps, we
noticed parking
lots filled with the cars of
those who drove

46:15.039 --> 46:19.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there when fighting again, but
are now forbidden
to leave.

46:19.343 --> 46:22.680 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Brigadier General Halkwat Rafaat
says they
could be a security threat.

46:22.713 --> 46:23.681 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
BRIG.

46:23.714 --> 46:25.216 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

46:25.249 --> 46:26.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HALKWAT RAFAAT, Iraq (through
translator):
Leaving the camp is forbidden.

46:26.350 --> 46:27.084 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They can't leave the camp until
Mosul is liberated.

46:27.118 --> 46:28.719 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We keep their I.D.s with us.

46:28.753 --> 46:31.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They will get their I.D.s when
they go back
to their homes.

46:31.255 --> 46:32.556 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: So, there's
nowhere to go?

46:32.590 --> 46:35.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They can't go home until they're
told that
they can go home?

46:35.559 --> 46:36.527 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
BRIG.

46:36.560 --> 46:37.795 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

46:37.828 --> 46:39.363 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
HALKWAT RAFAAT (through
translator): No, they
can't leave.

46:39.397 --> 46:42.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: I asked the
sisters, which was
worse, life here or under ISIS?

46:42.700 --> 46:46.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HIJRAN (through translator): Of
course life
here is better than ISIS.

46:46.470 --> 46:47.905 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ISIS terrified people.

46:47.938 --> 46:50.508 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They made us afraid of
everything.

46:50.541 --> 46:55.780 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we are trapped here, and
it's like we
traded one jail for another one.

46:55.813 --> 46:58.783 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We simply want to leave and live
our lives.

46:58.816 --> 47:01.485 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We know nothing about our
families in Mosul.

47:01.519 --> 47:03.254 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We don't know what is happening
there.

47:03.287 --> 47:07.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: And still they
come, despite
the harsh conditions.

47:07.358 --> 47:11.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We were there when 6-year-old
Dema arrived
from Mosul with her family off,
not even yet

47:11.929 --> 47:13.731 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
off the bus.

47:13.764 --> 47:19.170 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
"I want to say hi to my
grandparents in Kirkuk
and my grandparents in Irbil,"
she told me,

47:19.203 --> 47:21.939 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and then was overcome with
emotions.

47:21.972 --> 47:27.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They may be less than 100 miles
away, but
little does she know she likely
has no chance

47:27.945 --> 47:33.584 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of seeing them or of leaving
this camp anytime
soon.

47:33.617 --> 47:38.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Like most of the resilient
children we met,
she was all smiles when we saw
her again.

47:38.456 --> 47:39.623 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Are you happy here?

47:39.657 --> 47:41.625 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DEMA, 6 Years Old (through
translator): Yes.

47:41.659 --> 47:42.793 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MARCIA BIGGS: Why?

47:42.827 --> 47:44.795 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DEMA (through translator): There
is no bombing
here.

47:44.829 --> 47:47.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: So, what do you
want to do now?

47:47.998 --> 47:48.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DEMA (through translator): I
want to play.

47:48.999 --> 47:50.768 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCIA BIGGS: It was a universal
desire.

47:50.801 --> 47:56.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we left, in their tattered
clothes, most
without proper shoes, the
children wanted

