morning runs
will change their lives.

49:12.149 --> 49:16.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's the core mission of the
organization
Back on My Feet, using running
as a catalyst

49:16.220 --> 49:19.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to move people out of
homelessness and into
jobs.

49:19.190 --> 49:23.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as executive director,
Theresa Lynn,
puts it, showing up for these
runs is just

49:23.661 --> 49:25.429 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the beginning of charting a new
course.

49:25.462 --> 49:27.731 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
THERESA LYNN, Executive
Director, Back on
My Feet: The first step
obviously is running

49:27.765 --> 49:30.701 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
